nown as {{lang|fr|Sylvain Fr\u00e9con}}.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dargaud.com/oggy-et-les-cafards |title=Oggy and the Cockroaches in comics |author= |date= |publisher=Dargaud |accessdate=12 October 2012|language=French}}</ref>\n\n* 16 April 2010 : ''{{lang|fr|Plouf, prouf,}} vrooo !''\n* 5 November 2010 : {{lang|fr|Crac, boum, miaouuuuu !}}\n* 23 September 2011 : {{lang|fr|Bip...bip...bip...}}\n\nAn American comic was planned to be released in the summer of 2019. It was released on December 11, 2019, after being delayed two times.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://previewsworld.com/Catalog/AUG191530 |title = Oggy & the Cockroaches #1 CVR a Rankine (Aug191530)}}</ref> It is published by American Mythology Productions.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.comicon.com/2019/02/19/american-mythology-comic-series-celebrates-oggy-and-the-cockroachess-20th-anniversary/ | title=American Mythology Comic Series Celebrates Oggy and the Cockroaches's 20th Anniversary| date=19 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.comixology.com/Oggy-the-Cockroaches-1/digital-comic/803091?ref=Y29taWMvdmlldy9kZXNrdG9wL3NsaWRlckxpc3Qvc2VyaWVz | title=Oggy & the Cockroaches #1 - Comics by comiXology}}</ref>\n\n===Home media===\nFive DVDs came out in 2003 in the United States, with 12 episodes each. In 2005, several VHSes were released in New York City.\n\nOn 8 October 2008, a French DVD boxset of the complete first series, plus the pilot and the episode \"Working Cat\", is available. On 6 September 2010, three French DVD boxsets of the complete first, second, and third series are available. On July 2011, a French DVD boxset containing all episodes from seasons 1, 2 and 3 became available.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! # !! DVD name !! Release date\n|-\n| 1 || Volume 1 || {{Date|2003-11-04}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com/Oggy-Cockroaches-Vol-Artist-Provided/dp/B0000E2W0B/ref=sr_1_1?keywords=oggy+and+the+cockroaches&qid=1564813115&s=movies-tv&sr=1-1 |website=www.amazon.com